This paper reported the monitoring result of pathogenic vibrio from 1461 diarrhoea outpatients in Haikou city from April to November 1986. 438 strains of pathogenic vibri (29.98%) had been identified. Among them the Vibrio Parahemolyticus (14.99%) was more common and the next was non-0:1 V. Cholerae strains (11.84%). The features of attack-time, age, sex and clinical symptoms etc. were discussed.